 this history tell us about who we are? In addition to being a thoughtful philosophical companion, Samuelson is also a memorable tour guide, taking us on plenty of detours and pausing to linger over an afternoon Negroni, sample four classic Roman pastas, or explore the city’s best hidden gems. With Samuelson’s help, we understand why Rome has inspired philosophers such as Lucretius and Seneca, poets and artists such as Horace and Caravaggio, filmmakers like Fellini, and adventurers like Rosa Bathurst. This eclectic guidebook to Roman philosophy is for intrepid wanderers and armchair travelers alike—anyone who wants not just a change of scenery, but a change of soul.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPhilosophy, Ancient. 7aTravel / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107973290 cprintz978022682626440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226826257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226826257/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles